document_data.History:
Mira grew up rarely seeing her father, who was the head priest for a cell of Harpers operating on the southern [[Sword Coast]]. She apprenticed to antiquarians in [[Baldur's Gate]] as a teenager.{{Cite digital book/Lesser Evils|1664}} At some point, she became involved with the Zhentarim because they gave her access to ruins she could never find on her own.

In the {{YearlinkName|1478}}, Mira was posing as a mercenary guard for a [[Waterdeep|Waterdavian]] merchant who possessed a page from a [[magic|magical]] [[Netheril|Netherese]] book, the ''[[Book of Tarchamus]]''. After the page was sold to an agent of the [[Shadovar]], Mira helped her father steal the page and was able to locate the ancient Netherese [[Library of Tarchamus|library]] the page came from. Mira traveled to the library with her father and the [[tiefling]] sisters [[Farideh]] and [[Havilar]] and recovered the book. During their adventure, they destroyed the library and the [[undead]] within.

By the {{YearlinkName|1486}}, Mira had secretly joined the Harpers herself and acted as their spy inside the Zhentarim.{{Cite dragon/430/The Harpers of Waterdeep|36}}
